<item>
            <title>[LU-16493] recovery-small/144b fails with ZFS</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16493</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;the subtest expects 50 files each with 1K stripes can be created in 60 seconds which is not quite enough for ZFS. I did local measurements and observed:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;OST object precreation doesn&apos;t block creations (MDS has enough objects at any moment)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;MDS needs to update last_used file for each OST object used, i.e. 50*1000=50K times&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ZFS&apos;s writerecord and writerecord&apos;s declaration is still much slower compared to ldiskfs (2-3x slower)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
